    "answer_id" : 70837193,
    "question_id" : 16891182,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>you have two options:</strong></p>\n<p>cmd doesn't show the password on the screen while typing<br />\nso just type the correct passwd -and be careful- then press enter.</p>\n<p><strong>Or</strong>\njust use:</p>\n<pre><code>keytool -list -keystore 'keystoreName' -storepass 'type your keystore passwd'\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>and</strong> for Keys' full info, add <code>-v</code>:</p>\n<pre><code>keytool -v -list -keystore 'keystoreName' -storepass 'type your keystore passwd'\n</code></pre>\n"
